
'''Chuddies''' is a word which orginated from the north of [[India]] in approximately [[1760]] as slang term for underclothes (i.e. underwear). Men previously used the word chuddies instead of listing all their undergarments. The word first appeared in the [[United Kingdom]] in the comedy ''[[Goodness Gracious Me]]'' from which it gained in popularity. Recently the word was entered into the [[Oxford English Dictionary]], but was classed as Anglo-Indian rather than Indian.